tafsir[3]{c,v,t}:
  24,59,"The Arabic word Atiq, which has been used for the Kabah, is very meaningful for it implies."
  24,60,"Though the command is of a general nature, here it refers particularly to the prohibitions which are connected with the Sacred Mosque, Hajj, Umrah and Makkah. Incidentally, there is a subtle hint in it to the Quraish; who had driven out the Muslims from Makkah and debarred them from Hajj and violated the sanctity of the Ancient House by associating indecent, filthy, and ungodly rites with Hajj and the House in contradiction to the ways of Abraham."
  24,61,"“And the cattle have been made lawful for you” has been cited here for two objects."